<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-06-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-06-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="389" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d389">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 Lithuania/86a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in Lithuania (<persName type="to">Stafford</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 7</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-14">June 14,
                                    1932</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The Secretary of State refers to previous correspondence regarding
                                the President’s Proposal of June 20, 1931, for postponement of <pb facs="0726" n="606" xml:id="pg_606"/> intergovernmental debts
                                and transmits for the information of the Chargé d’Affaires copy of
                                the “Agreement between the Republic of Lithuania and the United
                                States of America, June 9, 1932”.<note n="34" xml:id="d389fn34">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Annual Report of the Secretary of the
                                        Treasury</hi>, 1932, pp. 297–298.</note>
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>